        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 12:09AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1209 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Colorado City, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dunn, Colorado City Airport, Inadale, Hermleigh, Loraine, Lake
Colorado City, Champion Creek Reservoir, Westbrook, Lake Colorado
City State Park, Buford, and Colorado City.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 206 and 228.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
